<h1 id="pointers">Pointers</h1>

<p>Python etc have a concept of a reference - a pointer-like thing to an object</p>
<ul>
  <li>in Java, objects arrays etc are references but primitives are not references.</li>
</ul>

<p>Chuk: ‚ÄúYou wont ask an F1 driver to ask slowly right. Sometimes you want the freedom to do stupid things [as an engineer].‚Äù</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>name := "fred"

&amp;name #gives you the address of a var 

*&amp;name == "fred" # gives you contents of the address 
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>This allows you to have double pointers that allow ‚Äúdynamic addressing‚Äù (TODO: look up)</p>

<p>And anything can be passed by reference or value into functions</p>

