<h2 id="initialise-project-as-a-go-project">Initialise project as a Go project</h2>
<p>Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">go mod init</code> in the directory where your project is. It should create a file called <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">go.mod</code>.</p>

<h2 id="my-first-go-program-">My first Go program :)</h2>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>package main

func main() {
    fmt.Println("hello, world")
}
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Run programs with <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">go run .</code> in the directory where your go program file is stored.</p>

<h2 id="boardgame-api">Boardgame API</h2>

<p>We are using the Search endpoint: https://www.boardgameatlas.com/api/docs/search</p>

<p>We need:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Search term</li>
  <li>Client id</li>
  <li>Limit (e.g. 10)</li>
  <li>Skip (e.g. 0)</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="compiling">Compiling</h2>
<p>Use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">go build .</code></p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">go run</code> is for devt purposes.</p>

